# Trail Overlay — Project Context

## Purpose
Next.js app to overlay mountain bike trails on maps. Users upload GPX rides, trim segments into reusable trails, tag difficulty/direction, organize into networks. Includes a Chrome extension that injects trail data into Strava.

## Stack
- Next.js 16 (App Router), React 19, TypeScript 5
- Leaflet 1.9.4 (map), Tailwind CSS 4
- PostgreSQL (pg driver), JWT sessions (jose)
- Strava OAuth, Vercel deployment

## Directory Layout
```
app/
  page.tsx              # Server wrapper
  ClientPage.tsx        # Main state container (rides, trails, networks, editMode)
  layout.tsx
  api/
    auth/strava/        # OAuth init + callback (upserts user, sets cookie)
    auth/logout/
    upload/             # POST GPX/ZIP → parse → insert rides
    trails/             # GET (CORS-open), POST
    trails/[id]/        # PATCH, DELETE
    rides/              # GET (auth required)
    networks/           # GET (CORS-open), POST
    networks/[id]/      # PATCH, DELETE
    health/
components/
  LeafletMap.tsx        # Interactive map; trail/ride/network rendering; trimming UI
  LeftDrawer.tsx        # Sidebar: upload, ride list, trail list, trim form, network list
  AuthButton.tsx
lib/
  db.ts                 # pg pool; query() / queryOne()
  auth.ts               # getSessionUser() / getSessionUserId()
  session.ts            # JWT encrypt/decrypt; 30-day cookie
  gpx-utils.ts          # GPX + ZIP parsing (gpxparser, jszip)
  geo-utils.ts          # Haversine distance, elevation gain
  types.ts              # Shared interfaces
migrations/             # 001–006 SQL migrations
browser-extension/      # Chrome extension (content.js, background.js, popup)
```

## Database Tables
| Table | Key Columns |
|-------|-------------|
| users | id, strava_athlete_id, name, profile_picture, access/refresh_token, token_expires_at |
| rides | id, user_id, name, distance, elevation, polyline (JSONB), point_count, timestamp |
| trails | id, name, difficulty, direction, polyline (JSONB), distance_km, elevation_gain_ft, notes, source, source_ride_id, uploaded_by_user_id |
| networks | id, name, polygon (JSONB) |
| network_trails | network_id, trail_id (junction) |

## Key Types (lib/types.ts)
```ts
Ride          { id, name, distance, elevation, polyline: [lat,lon][], timestamp, pointCount }
Trail         { id, name, difficulty, direction, polyline, distanceKm, elevationGainFt, notes, source, sourceRideId, uploadedByEmail, createdAt }
Network       { id, name, polygon: [lat,lon][], trailIds, createdAt }
TrimSegment   { ride, startIndex, endIndex, polyline, distanceKm, elevationGainFt }
SessionUser   { id, name, profilePicture, stravaAthleteId }
EditMode      = 'add-trail' | 'edit-trail' | 'refine-trail' | 'add-network' | 'edit-network' | null
difficulty    = 'easy' | 'intermediate' | 'hard' | 'not_set'
direction     = 'one-way' | 'out-and-back' | 'loop' | 'not_set'
```

## Env Vars
| Var | Notes |
|-----|-------|
| DATABASE_URL | Postgres connection string |
| STRAVA_CLIENT_ID | OAuth app ID |
| STRAVA_CLIENT_SECRET | Server-only |
| SESSION_SECRET | 32-byte hex for JWT |
| NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL | Base URL (browser-visible) |
| NODE_ENV | Controls cookie security |

## Architecture Notes
- Single Next.js/Vercel deployment (no separate API server)
- Leaflet loaded via `dynamic()` with SSR disabled
- CORS open on `/api/trails` and `/api/networks` for browser extension
- Trail trimming: client picks start/end indices on ride polyline → haversine math → save as trail
- GPX parsed server-side on upload; polylines stored as JSONB
- Browser extension injects into `strava.com/maps/create/*`, fetches trails from API

